<HEADLINE>
TAIWAN-VATICAN PARTNERSHIP FOR CHARITY TO GROW CLOSER: PRESIDENT
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  April 19 (CNA) 04/20/07  10:53:35 (By Sofia Wu)
</P>
<P>
President Chen Shui-bian said Thursday that partnership between
Taiwan and the Vatican on issues of peace and charity will grow
closer in the years ahead as the two sides share common values
and political convictions.
</P>
<P>
Chen made the remarks while attending a reception at the Embassy
of the Holy See in Taipei marking the second anniversary of Pope
Benedict XVII's ascension to the papal throne.
</P>
<P>
In addition to extending felicitations on the pope's crowning
anniversary on behalf of the Republci of china government and
people, Chen also expressed his keen hope that Taiwan and the
Holy See can further expand engagements  to boost mutual
understanding  and friendship.
</P>
<P>
Noting that Taiwan is more than willing to assist other countries
in economic development, Chen said Taiwan and the Vatican should
strengthen cooperation and partnership  in promoting peace and
offering humanitarian aid and disaster relief to disadvantaged
people around the world.
</P>
<P>
The Holy See is the only European country that maintains formal
diplomatic ties with Taiwan.
</P>
